Question Given two non-negative integers, num1 and num2 represented as string, return the sum of num1 and num2 as a string.
You must solve the problem without using any built-in library for handling large integers (such as BigInteger). You must also not convert the inputs to integers directly.
Examples Input: num1 = &ldquo;11&rdquo;, num2 = &ldquo;123&rdquo;
Output: &ldquo;134&rdquo;
Input: num1 = &ldquo;456&rdquo;, num2 = &ldquo;77&rdquo;
Output: &ldquo;533&rdquo;
Input: num1 = &ldquo;0&rdquo;, num2 = &ldquo;0&rdquo;
